  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic songs in Malayalam?",
  "response": "Ah, Malayalam cinema and music are full of romance! It's tough to pick just a few, as \"romantic\" is subjective, but here are some of the most beloved and often considered the most romantic Malayalam songs, categorized a bit for variety:\n\n**Timeless Classics (Golden Era):**\n\n*   **\"Poomaram Choodi\" (Yakshi):** K.J. Yesudas's voice is pure magic in this melancholic yet beautiful love song. The imagery of the song makes it a classic.\n*   **\"Manjil Kulichu\" (Kochu Kochu Mohangal):** A beautiful melody rendered by K.J. Yesudas and K.S. Chitra.\n*   **\"Oru Dalimozhi\" (Angane Oru Avadhikkalathu):** A timeless rendition by K.J. Yesudas, set in a backdrop of love and separation.\n*   **\"Thamarakkannan Urangenam\" (Agnisakshi):** This is a lullaby for a husband from a wife, pure intimacy.\n*   **\"Surumayezhuthiya Mizhikal\" (Kunjalimarackar):** Set on the backdrop of arabian sea, with the voice of P.Maduri and K.J. Yesudas.\n\n**Evergreen Hits (80s and 90s):**\n\n*   **\"Chembarathi Poovu\" (Dwani):**  K.S. Chithra's voice and the gentle melody create a feeling of pure, innocent love.\n*   **\"Karmukilin Kinnaramo\" (Mazha):** A sensual and romantic song depicting the magic of the rain. A masterpiece by K.S. Chitra.\n*   **\"Poove Poochoodi Vaa\" (My Dear Muthachan):** A feel good melody by K.J. Yesudas and K.S. Chitra.\n*   **\"Ee Ravilum\" (Nirnayam):** The most celebrated song in the history of Malayalam music, with an unmatched rendition by K.J. Yesudas and K.S. Chithra.\n*   **\"Enthe Nee Ente Kunjatte\" (Sasneham):** A soothing melody that would immerse anyone in a romantic vibe.\n*   **\"Aaromal\" (Oru Cheru Punchiri):** A magical melody that would evoke the emotions of every listener.\n*   **\"Kannodu Kannaaya Nottam\" (Ghazal):**  A classic romantic song, filled with longing and devotion. The perfect ghazal to portray intimacy.\n*   **\"Rajahamsame\" (Chamaram):** Another great melody, where the singer compares his love to a swan.\n\n**Modern Romantic Songs (2000s - Present):**\n\n*   **\"Malare\" (Premam):** Undoubtedly one of the most popular romantic songs of recent times, capturing the feeling of young love.\n*   **\"Pathukalpanakal\" (Adam Joan):** Beautifully sung by Shweta Mohan, this song is dreamy and romantic.\n*   **\"Vathikkalu Vellaripravu\" (Salt N' Pepper):**  A playful and quirky, yet utterly romantic song.\n*   **\"Hey Jude\" (Hey Jude):** A melodious masterpiece that soothes the listeners, especially the voice of Gayathri.\n*   **\"Uyire\" (Godha):**  A beautiful song with a catchy tune, perfect for expressing love.\n*   **\"Doore Doore\" (God's Own Country):**  A romantic song with a touch of melancholy.\n*   **\"Aararo\" (C U Soon):** A hauntingly beautiful melody that portrays the love for a child.\n*   **\"Chillane\" (North 24 Kaatham):** A soulful melody by Karthik that everyone can relate to.\n*   **\"Thennal Nilavinte\" (Anwar):** A soft and romantic song with amazing visuals.\n*   **\"Hridayam Ekantha\" (Oru Naal Varum):** Set in a backdrop of a scenic beauty, this is an amazing romantic song.\n\n**Important Considerations When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Lyrics:** Malayalam song lyrics often use beautiful metaphors and imagery to express love. Pay attention to the meaning!\n*   **Context:** The meaning and impact of a song can be deeply influenced by the movie it's from and the story it tells.\n\nThis list is just a starting point. There are countless other beautiful and romantic Malayalam songs. The best way to discover your favorites is to explore different eras, composers, and singers! Happy listening!\n",
